                  </persName>
            , that he was of the Stock Exchange, but not a member, that he attended at the Rotunda - that he did not know where he lived - he knew him only as attending the Rotunda - that he was a young man, about thirty years of age, and that he had accepted his attestation of identity before, but that he did not know where he resided or might be heard of. I then turned to the transfer of the 23d of March, 1821, of 1800 l. 5 per cents. from 
               <persName id="t18210912-64-person689">
                  John 
                  Penn
